dataIdInfo.idPurp: These subbasins are a subdivision of the watershed area draining to Wachusett Reservoir based primarily on the 54 EQ (DCR) tributary sampling locations, both past and present. An additional 31 subbasins were delineated so that the entire watershed was divided into subbasins of approximately equal size. This subbasin representation was created with the intention that it would be used for water quality analyses and compiling watershed data by sub-watershed areas.

report.measDesc: Although these subbasin boundaries were field verified in some cases, subbasin boundaries were not drawn at a parcel level scale and were not surveyed. Drainage delineations specific to a single parcel or project should be checked for accuracy and/or field verified and surveyed if necessary.

These subbasins were delineated using the LiDAR DEM for the Nashua River Basin (circa 2011) available from Mass GIS, which has a vertical accuracy of 0.172 m (0.56 ft) and a cell size of 1x1 meter. This data was resampled to a 5x5 meter horizontal resolution to reduce processing time.

prcStep.stepDesc: These subbasins were delineated using the LiDAR DEM for the Nashua River Basin (circa 2011) available from Mass GIS, which has a vertical accuracy of 0.172 m (0.56 ft) and a cell size of 1x1 meter. This data was resampled to a 5x5 meter horizontal resolution to reduce processing time. Several ArcGIS tools were then used to modify this 5x5 meter DEM into a hydrologically conditioned DEM. Sinks were filled and a flow direction raster was rendered from the DEM. Flow accumulation was then rendered using the flow direction raster. Drainage infrastructure (culverts, stormdrains, etc), were incorporated by using the Topo to Raster tool, which altered the DEM, which in turn alters the flow direction and flow accumulation raster. The Topo to Raster tool was used iteratively while updating the Arc feature class, so that drainage was forced to follow engineered subsurface flow paths (under bridges, into storm drains and through culverts). Upon the completion of the hydrologically conditioned DEM ArcHydro tools were used to automatically delineate subbasins using the water quality monitoring stations as pour points. 54 subbasins resulted from this inititial delineation. 31 additional subbasins were created by selecting other pour points for major tributaries and larger ponds and reservoirs. The drainage to the Wachusett reservoir was divided into sections for each of the major basins.
